HOUSE BILL 1131
J1, J2, J3 6lr1172
By: Delegates Lopez, Alston, Behler, Crutchfield, Feldmark, Foley, D. Jones, Kerr,
Lehman, Lewis, Martinez, Mireku–North, Palakovich Carr, Patterson,
Shetty, Solomon, Spiegel, Terrasa, White Holland, Wilkins, Wims, Wolek,
and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Judiciary and Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Pregnancy Loss – Prohibited Actions
3 (Pregnancy Outcome Protection Act)
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting individuals who experienced a pregnancy loss from being
5 subject to investigation, civil liability, or criminal prosecution except under certain
6 circumstances; establishing a private right of action for a violation of a certain
7 prohibition against investigations of pregnancy loss; providing that an incidence of
8 pregnancy loss does not constitute probable cause to issue a certain search warrant,
9 except under certain circumstances; prohibiting certain providers from being subject
10 to investigation, criminal penalty, or civil liability for supporting a patient who is
11 experiencing a pregnancy loss or after a pregnancy loss; prohibiting certain providers
12 from reporting on or disclosing a certain medical record related to pregnancy loss,
13 except under certain circumstances; and generally relating to prohibited actions
14 related to pregnancy loss.
15 BY adding to
16 Article – Health – General
17 Section 20–217 through 20–220 to be under the new part “Part V. Pregnancy Loss”
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
21 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
22 Article – Health – General
23 20–215. RESERVED.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
